'''''Amuropaludina pachya''''' is a [[species]] of [[freshwater snail]] with a [[gill]] and an [[operculum (gastropod)|operculum]], an [[Aquatic animal|aquatic]] [[gastropod]] [[mollusk]] in the family [[Viviparidae]].

== Distribution ==
This species is found in the central and lower parts of the [[Amur River]] basin, in [[List of non-marine molluscs of Russia|Russia]].<ref name="IUCN 2011"/> The [[type locality (biology)|type locality]] is the Amur River ("le fleuve Amour").<ref name="Bourguignat 1860"/>

Major threats include [[river pollution]].<ref name="IUCN 2011"/>

[[File:Amuropaludina pachya shell 2.png|left|thumb|Drawing of a lateral view of the shell of ''Amuropaludina pachya'']]

== Description ==
The width of the shell is 21&nbsp;mm.<ref name="Bourguignat 1860"/> The height of the shell is 34&nbsp;mm.<ref name="Bourguignat 1860"/>

